trend_summary: Built-up land grew steadily decade on decade, filling forest clearings and former farmland, especially along the main highway axis and in the east. Expansion is mainly low-rise housing and retail, so the landscape stays suburban; the western floodplain remains largely green. Road density and commercial roofs increased, while several riparian strips show fresh vegetation after channel works.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of residential subdivisions in the central-north, replacing wooded parcels.
